<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9d28168-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s390h–19"><num value="390h–19">§ 390h–19.</num><heading> Williamson County, Texas, water recycling and reuse project</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc9d28169-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s390h–19/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorization</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary, in cooperation with the Lower Colorado River Authority, Texas, is authorized to participate in the design, planning, and construction of permanent facilities to reclaim and reuse water in Williamson County, Texas.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc9d2816a-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s390h–19/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Cost share</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Federal share of the costs of the project described in subsection (a) shall not exceed 25 percent of the total cost.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc9d2816b-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s390h–19/c"><num value="c" class="bold">(c)</num><heading class="bold"> Limitation</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall not provide funds for the operation and maintenance of the project described in subsection (a).</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idc9d2816c-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/102/575/tXVI/s1637">Pub. L. 102–575, title XVI, § 1637</ref>, formerly § 1636, as added <ref href="/us/pl/108/316/s1/b">Pub. L. 108–316, § 1(b)</ref>, <date date="2004-10-05">Oct. 5, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/1202">118 Stat. 1202</ref>; renumbered § 1637, <ref href="/us/pl/109/70/s2/a/1">Pub. L. 109–70, § 2(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="2005-09-21">Sept. 21, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/2009">119 Stat. 2009</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
